00:27:05.190 --> 00:27:11.980 position:56%
the desire for land and of course
cold trapping, et cetera, et cetera,

00:27:11.980 --> 00:27:18.100
could these Indian Wars
really have been avoided?

00:27:21.000 --> 00:27:27.980
&gt;&gt; Peter Cozzens: Some of them
could have been, if not avoided,

00:27:27.980 --> 00:27:31.960
at least ameliorated, because
some of the Indian Wars

00:27:31.960 --> 00:27:35.190
like the Nez Perce
War involved tribes

00:27:35.190 --> 00:27:39.270
that were already partly
acculturated.

00:27:39.270 --> 00:27:43.600
But on the Plains, the Great
Plains where the majority

00:27:43.600 --> 00:27:47.600
of the conflict took place I don't
think they could have been avoided

00:27:47.600 --> 00:27:50.990
because you had tribes
like the Cheyanne.

00:27:50.990 --> 00:27:56.980
The Cheyanne numbered only about
3500 people yet during the time

00:27:56.980 --> 00:27:59.760
of which we speak they claimed

00:27:59.760 --> 00:28:06.970
as their traditional hunting lands
Eastern Colorado, Western Kansas,

00:28:06.970 --> 00:28:12.920
Western Nebraska, Northern
modern-day Oklahoma

00:28:12.920 --> 00:28:15.240
and Southern Wyoming.

00:28:15.240 --> 00:28:19.200
Now it just wasn't reasonable
to expect the Whites,

00:28:19.200 --> 00:28:26.760
you know a population of 38
million to turn over the equivalent

00:28:26.760 --> 00:28:29.870
of maybe what, maybe three
modern western states

00:28:29.870 --> 00:28:35.940
to 3500 essentially
hunters and gatherers.

00:28:35.940 --> 00:28:44.460
So, a good portion affect at least
half of the Plains Indians did try

00:28:44.460 --> 00:28:48.790
to make the transition
peacefully to a different way of,

00:28:48.790 --> 00:28:53.270
to an agricultural way
of life, but for a number

00:28:53.270 --> 00:28:59.050
of reasons the success
was partial at best.

00:28:59.050 --> 00:29:02.460
There were strong traditionalist
factions like those led

00:29:02.460 --> 00:29:05.260
by Crazy Horse, Sitting
Bull that didn't want

00:29:05.260 --> 00:29:07.860
to fight the Whites they just
wanted to pursue their old way

00:29:07.860 --> 00:29:10.220
of living and chasing the buffalo.

00:29:10.220 --> 00:29:13.470
But that was, unfortunately
that was just.

00:29:13.470 --> 00:29:21.040
It was just incongruent with
such a huge western population.

00:29:21.040 --> 00:29:25.180
So, some of the conflicts
at least were inevitable

00:29:25.180 --> 00:29:28.790
and it was absolutely
inevitable that that way

00:29:28.790 --> 00:29:32.140
of life was going to
have to give way.

00:29:32.140 --> 00:29:34.570
Yes sir?

00:29:34.570 --> 00:29:39.290
&gt;&gt; You look at Western civilization
and you see what happened

00:29:39.290 --> 00:29:43.570
when something else different,
events sort of that's happened.

00:29:43.570 --> 00:29:49.930
It was Genghis Khan who unified
the Mongols and nomadic tribes

00:29:49.930 --> 00:29:54.620
and essentially you know attacked
civilization quite successfully.

00:29:54.620 --> 00:29:57.910
At what point, if the Indians
had gotten a leader like that

00:29:57.910 --> 00:30:02.360
who could unify them, and would
it have been able to really wipe

00:30:02.360 --> 00:30:07.550
out the civilization, seriously
impede it for many centuries?

00:30:07.550 --> 00:30:11.410
At what point, would it
be before the Civil War?

00:30:11.410 --> 00:30:12.710
Would [inaudible]?

00:30:12.710 --> 00:30:16.010
Would it have been
later, at what point?

00:30:16.010 --> 00:30:17.320
&gt;&gt; Peter Cozzens: That's
